    • Enum Constant Detail

      • ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_UNEXPECTED_RESPONSE

        public static final AdobePhotoErrorCode ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_UNEXPECTED_RESPONSE
        A response from the server did not match its anticipated form and therefore could not be processed.

        This could be caused by an unexpected HTTP response code or missing/malformed data. Typically this indicates a (temporary) problem with the server or the network.

      • ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_CONFLICTING_CHANGES

        public static final AdobePhotoErrorCode ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_CONFLICTING_CHANGES
        Both the local copy and the copy on the server have been modified.

        This error can happen when trying to push local changes to an asset on the server.

      • ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_FILE_READ_FAILURE

        public static final AdobePhotoErrorCode ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_FILE_READ_FAILURE
        Reading from a file has failed.

        This error can happen when a file fails to upload because it can't be found or read.

      • ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_FILE_WRITE_FAILURE

        public static final AdobePhotoErrorCode ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_FILE_WRITE_FAILURE
        Writing to a file has failed.

        This error can happen when a file fails to download because it can't be written to local storage.

      • ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_EXCEEDED_QUOTA

        public static final AdobePhotoErrorCode ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_EXCEEDED_QUOTA
        An upload has failed because it would have exceeded the quota on the account.

      • ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_MISSING_JSON_DATA

        public static final AdobePhotoErrorCode ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_MISSING_JSON_DATA
        An attempt was made to use an empty JSON payload.

      • ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_MEDIA

        public static final AdobePhotoErrorCode ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_MEDIA
        The data returned by the server does not match the requested type. This error typically occurs when requesting a rendition of a file type that does not have one, e.g., a .JSON or .DMG file.

      • ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_NOT_ENTITLED_TO_SERVICE

        public static final AdobePhotoErrorCode ADOBE_PHOTO_ERROR_NOT_ENTITLED_TO_SERVICE
        The requested action or component isn't allowed by the entitlements defined for the currently logged in user. This error typically occurs when attempting to access a service that is not enabled by the user's account administrator.
